🛰️ OSI Model (Open Systems Interconnection Model)
Definition:
OSI ek conceptual framework hai jo explain karta hai ki data kaise ek device se dusre device tak travel karta hai, 7 layers ke through.

🏛 Layers of OSI Model (Top → Bottom)
7. Application Layer
End-user ke closest layer.
Human-readable data handle karta hai (jaise form input, POST request).
Example: Browser → Node.js server (username & password bhejna).
Protocols: HTTP, HTTPS, FTP, SMTP.

6. Presentation Layer
Data ko transform karta hai → readable & secure form mein.
Tasks:
Serialization (e.g., JSON.stringify).
Compression (data chhota karna).
Encryption/Decryption (security ke liye).
Example: HTTPS encryption, data compression.

5. Session Layer
Do devices ke beech connection/session manage karta hai.
Session create/maintain/destroy karna.
Example: TCP connections, remote login sessions.
Data pe yaha koi change nahi hota.

4. Transport Layer
Data ko chhote segments mein todta hai.
Port numbers assign karta hai (Source & Destination dono ke).
Reliable delivery ensure karta hai (TCP) ya fast delivery (UDP).
Example:
Segment: Source Port 54321 → Destination Port 4000
Service to Service delivery.

3. Network Layer
Segment + IP addresses add → Packet banata hai.
Source & Destination IP assign hota hai.
Example:
TCP:54321
Source IP: 192.168.0.5
Destination IP: 142.3.4.1
End to End delivery.

2. Data Link Layer
Packet + MAC addresses add → Frame banata hai.
Source & Destination MAC assign hota hai.
(Router ke MAC use hote hain, end device ke nahi).
Example:
Source MAC: 24-9A-43-2B
Dest. MAC: 1A-42-F9-4B
Hop to Hop delivery.

1. Physical Layer
Frames ko physical signals mein convert karta hai (electrical, optical, radio waves).
Data cables, WiFi signals, fiber optics.
Yehi se data device se physically nikalta hai.

📦 Encapsulation & Decapsulation
Encapsulation: Jab data Application layer → Physical layer tak jata hai, har layer apni info add karti hai.
Decapsulation: Jab data destination device par aata hai, har layer apni info remove karke asli data Application tak pahuchati hai.

🔑 Delivery Types
Hop to Hop delivery → Data Link Layer (Layer 2).
End to End delivery → Network Layer (Layer 3).
Service to Service delivery → Transport Layer (Layer 4).

📌 Important Notes
Node.js app → Application layer mein hoti hai, lekin indirectly Presentation, Session & Transport layer concepts ko bhi use karti hai.
OSI model = theoretical model.
Practically hum mostly TCP/IP model use karte hain.